pylimma
=======

Copyright (C) 2026 John Mulvey

This product is a Python port of R limma (Linear Models for Microarray and
Omics Data), the most widely used Bioconductor package for differential
expression analysis. Substantial portions of pylimma's algorithms,
parameter semantics, and statistical methods are derived from the R
implementation.

The Python port is licensed under the GNU General Public License version 3
or any later version (GPL-3.0-or-later), in conformance with R limma's
licence grant of "GPL (>=2)".

